{"title_page": "Merzak Allouache", "text_new": "{{short description|Algerian film director}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n|image = \n| name         = Merzak Allouache\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1944|10|6|df=yes}}\n| birth_place  = [[Algiers]], Algeria\n| death_date   =\n| death_place  =\n| occupation   = Film director\n| yearsactive  = 1976-present\n}}\n\n'''Merzak Allouache''' (born 6 October 1944) is an Algerian [[film director]] and [[screenwriter]]. He has directed 18 films since 1976. His 1976 film ''[[Omar Gatlato]]'' was entered into the [[10th Moscow International Film Festival]] where it won the Silver Prize.<ref name=\"Moscow1977\">{{cite web|url=http://www.moscowfilmfestival.ru/miff34/eng/archives/?year=1977 |title=10th Moscow International Film Festival (1977) |accessdate=13 January 2013 |work=MIFF |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130116194935/http://www.moscowfilmfestival.ru/miff34/eng/archives/?year=1977 |archivedate=16 January 2013 }}</ref> His 1996 ''[[Salut cousin!]]'' was [[Submissions for the 69th Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|submitted to the 69th Academy Awards]] in the category of [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]].<ref name=\"69thSubmissions\">{{cite web|title=39 Countries Hoping for Oscar Nominations |publisher=[[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]] |date=13 November 1996 |url=//www.oscars.org/pressreleases/96.11.13.html |accessdate=5 October 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/19990209110950/http://www.oscars.org/pressreleases/96.11.13.html |archivedate=9 February 1999 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nHis 2011 film ''[[Normal!]]'' won the award for Best Film at the 2011 [[Doha Tribeca Film Festival]].<ref name=\"al-akhbar.com\">{{cite web |url=http://english.al-akhbar.com/content/algerian-filmmaker-merzak-allouache-struggles-censorship-after-long-career |title=Algerian Filmmaker Merzak Allouache Struggles with Censorship After Long Career |accessdate=6 April 2012 |work=al-akhbar.com |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304063646/http://english.al-akhbar.com/content/algerian-filmmaker-merzak-allouache-struggles-censorship-after-long-career |archive-date=4 March 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In 2012, his film ''[[The Repentant]]'' was screened in the [[Directors' Fortnight]] section at the [[2012 Cannes Film Festival]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Leffler|first=Rebecca|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/michel-gondry-cannes-film-festival-directors-fortnight-314985|title=Cannes 2012: Michel Gondry\u2019s 'The We & The I' to Open Director's Fortnight|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=26 May 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.quinzaine-realisateurs.com/2012-selection-h201.html |title=2012 Selection |work=quinzaine-realisateurs.com |publisher=[[Directors' Fortnight]] |accessdate=26 May 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120426224019/http://www.quinzaine-realisateurs.com/2012-selection-h201.html |archivedate=26 April 2012 }}</ref> It won the [[FIPRESCI]] Award for Best Asian Film at the [[International Film Festival of Kerala#IFFK 2012|17th International Film Festival of Kerala]].<ref>{{Cite news|last= |first= |url=http://english.manoramaonline.com/cgi-bin/MMOnline.dll/portal/ep/contentView.do?contentId=13032215&tabId=1&programId=11565535 |title=Curtains down on IFFK, Sta. Nina bags Suvarna Chakoram |work=[[Malayala Manorama]] |date=14 December 2012 |accessdate=14 December 2012 }}{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nHe was born in [[Algiers]].\n\n==Selected filmography==\n* ''[[Omar Gatlato]]'' (1976)\n* ''[[Mughamarat batal]]'' (1979)\n* ''[[Homme qui regardait les fen\u00eatres, L']]'' (1986)\n* ''[[Un amour \u00e0 Paris]]'' (1987)\n* ''[[Apr\u00e8s-Octobre, L']]'' (1989)\n* ''[[Bab El-Oued City]]'' (1994)\n* ''[[Lumi\u00e8re and Company|Lumi\u00e8re et compagnie]]'' (1995)\n* ''[[Dans la d\u00e9capotable]]'' (1996)\n* ''[[Salut cousin!]]'' (1996)\n* ''[[Alger-Beyrouth: Pour m\u00e9moire]]'' (1998) (TV)\n* ''[[\u00c0 bicyclette]]'' (2001) (TV)\n* ''[[Autre monde, L']]'' (2001)\n* ''[[Chouchou (film)|Chouchou]]'' (2003)\n* ''[[Bab el web]]'' (2005)\n* ''[[Tamanrasset (film)|Tamanrasset]]'' (2008) (TV)\n* ''[[Harragas]]'' (2009)\n* ''[[Normal!]]'' (2011)\n* ''[[The Repentant]]'' (2012)\n* ''[[The Rooftops (film)|The Rooftops]]'' (2013)\n* ''[[Madame Courage]]'' (2015)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* Will Higbee, \"Merzak Allouache: (Self)Censorship, Social Critique, and the Limits of Political Engagement in Contemporary Algerian Cinema\" in: Josef Gugler (ed.), ''Ten Arab Filmmakers: Political Dissent and Social Critique'', Indiana University Press, 2015, {{ISBN|978-0-253-01644-7}}, pp. 188-212\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|0021577|Merzak Allouache}}\n*[http://www.lib.berkeley.edu/MRC/euroimmigrantsbib.html#allouache Merzak Allouache Bibliography (via UC Berkeley)]\n{{Merzak Allouache}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Allouache, Merzak}}\n[[Category:1944 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Algerian film directors]]\n[[Category:People from Algiers]]\n[[Category:Algerian screenwriters]]\n{{Algeria-film-director-stub}}\n{{Screen-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Algerian film director}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n|image = \n| name         = Merzak Allouache\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1944|10|6|df=yes}}\n| birth_place  = [[Algiers]], Algeria\n| death_date   =\n| death_place  =\n| occupation   = Film director\n| yearsactive  = 1976-present\n}}\n\n'''Merzak Allouache''' (born 6 October 1944) is an Algerian [[film director]] and [[screenwriter]]. He has directed 18 films since 1976. His 1976 film ''[[Omar Gatlato]]'' was entered into the [[10th Moscow International Film Festival]] where it won the Silver Prize.<ref name=\"Moscow1977\">